    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban sale of filtered cigarette butts in UK by 2020",
        "additional_details": "According to\u00a0data collected by Ocean Conservancy, approximately 60 million cigarette filters have been collected since the 1980s.\r\n\r\nThis massively exceeds the number of plastic bags, food wrappers, drinks bottles or straws cleaned up from our oceans.\r\n\r\nSome dispose of their filters directly on the beach causing environmental harm which has damaging knock-on effects.\r\n\r\nhttps://www.google.com/amp/s/amp.businessinsider.com/new-study-shows-cigarettes-are-single-largest-source-of-ocean-trash-2018-9",
        "background": "Cigarette butts are non-biodegradable and release toxic chemicals into the sea.\r\n\r\nThey are the most numerous kind of pollutant there are in our oceans and on our planet.\r\n\r\nPlease save our marine ecosystems by urging our governments to ban the sale of all cigarette butts by 2020 in th UK.",
